@startuml
title Viaverse Search / SEO / Growth — Class Model

class SearchDocument {
  id: UUID
  entityType: REQUEST | WORKER | BUSINESS | SEO_PAGE
  entityId: UUID
  title: String
  summary: String
  categoryIds: Set<CategoryId>
  geo: ApproxGeo
  visibility: Visibility
  trustSignal: Decimal
  updatedAt: Instant
}

class SearchQuery {
  text: String?
  categoryId: CategoryId?
  area: AreaFilter?
  budget: BudgetFilter?
  locale: Locale
  sort: SortMode
  page: PageRequest
}

class RankingScore {
  relevance: Decimal
  trust: Decimal
  freshness: Decimal
  distance: Decimal
  availability: Decimal
  sponsoredBoost: Decimal
  finalScore: Decimal
  reasonCodes: List<String>
}

class SeoPage {
  id: UUID
  slug: String
  locale: Locale
  pageType: CATEGORY_CITY | SERVICE
  canonicalUrl: String
  schemaJson: Json
  status: SeoPageStatus
  updatedAt: Instant
}

class SearchAnalyticsEvent {
  id: UUID
  accountId: AccountId?
  sessionId: String
  queryHash: String
  resultIds: List<UUID>
  eventType: IMPRESSION | CLICK | CONVERSION
  createdAt: Instant
}

class GrowthExperiment {
  id: UUID
  key: String
  variant: String
  segmentRule: String
  status: ExperimentStatus
  startedAt: Instant
  endedAt: Instant?
}

class SearchPolicy {
  canIndexEntity()
  canExposePublicly()
  applyRankingGates()
  applySponsoredConstraints()
  localizeResult()
}

class SearchEvents {
  EntityIndexed
  EntityRemovedFromIndex
  SearchPerformed
  SearchClicked
  SeoPageUpdated
  ExperimentAssigned
}

SearchQuery ..> SearchDocument : matches
SearchDocument --> RankingScore : scored as
RankingScore --> SeoPage : can feed SEO ranking
SearchPolicy ..> SearchDocument : gates
SearchPolicy ..> RankingScore : ranking policy
SearchAnalyticsEvent --> GrowthExperiment : measures
GrowthExperiment ..> RankingScore : variant affects
SearchDocument ..> SearchEvents : emits
SearchAnalyticsEvent ..> SearchEvents : emits
SeoPage ..> SearchEvents : emits

note bottom
SearchDocument is a projection, not source-of-truth.
It can be rebuilt from domain events and public approved entities.
end note
@enduml
